    "reasoning": "To implement a dual-edge triggered flip-flop, we must recognize that standard Verilog does not support 'always @(posedge clk or negedge clk)' as a legal sensitivity list. Therefore, we need to build a circuit that achieves the same behavior using only single-edge triggered flip-flops. We'll use two flip-flops: one triggered on the positive edge of the clock and another on the negative edge, combined with a multiplexer to select the appropriate output based on the current clock edge. First, we register the input 'd' on both clock edges using separate DFFs. Then, we use a mux to select between these two values depending on whether the current clock edge is positive or negative. Since we cannot directly detect the clock edge in the sensitivity list, we'll store the previous value of the clock to determine the edge transition. A register 'clk_prev' is used to store the last value of the clock. In the always block, we check if the clock changed from 0 to 1 (positive edge) or 1 to 0 (negative edge) and accordingly select the data from either the positive or negative edge DFF. Additionally, we initialize the internal registers to ensure they have defined values during simulation start.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input d,\n    output q\n);\n\n    logic d_pos_edge;\n    logic d_neg_edge;\n    logic clk_prev;\n\n    // Register input d on positive edge of clock\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        d_pos_edge <= d;\n    end\n\n    // Register input d on negative edge of clock\n    always @(negedge clk) begin\n        d_neg_edge <= d;\n    end\n\n    // Determine clock edge and select appropriate data\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (clk_prev == 0 && clk == 1)\n            q = d_pos_edge;\n        else if (clk_prev == 1 && clk == 0)\n            q = d_neg_edge;\n        else\n            q = d_pos_edge; // default case to prevent X\n    end\n\n    // Store previous clock value\n    always @(posedge clk or negedge clk) begin\n        clk_prev <= clk;\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
